## Architecture

- Flutter talks only to `API_BASE_URL` (HTTPS in prod) тАФ never to Postgres directly.
- Backend: `backend/app/` FastAPI routers `auth`, `courts`, `profiles`, `uploads`.
- Local dev: `docker compose -f backend/docker-compose.dev.yml up -d`.

## Flutter integration

- `AppConfig.useLegacySupabase` from `--dart-define=USE_LEGACY_SUPABASE` (default `true`).
- When `false`: use `lib/repositories/*` + `ApiClient` with Bearer token from `TokenStorage`.
- New features: add API route + repository method; do not add `Supabase.instance.client` calls.

## Auth endpoints

- `POST /auth/register`, `/auth/login`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/logout`
- Passwords: Argon2id server-side only.

## Courts / profiles / uploads

- `GET /courts` тАФ approved courts
- `POST /courts` тАФ authenticated create
- `GET /profiles/me`, `PUT /profiles/me`
- `POST /uploads/presign` тАФ B2 presigned upload (JWT)

## Deprecated

- Direct Supabase table access for new code тАФ see `supabase-services.mdc` (legacy only).
